gression\": 0.9,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.93,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.88,\n      \"feedback\": \"Reasonable pathway based on the reported equilibrium relationship between glycolonitrile-derived reduced intermediates and serine nitrile in cyanometallate chemistry. The main limitation is that rxn_009 compresses a more complex equilibrium manifold into one node and may overstate directness.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_009\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Represent rxn_009 as an equilibrium or multistep transformation rather than a single direct conversion\",\n        \"Specify reductive and imine-forming substeps more explicitly\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P8\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_001\": 0.55,\n        \"rxn_003\": 0.91,\n        \"rxn_005\": 0.94,\n        \"rxn_006\": 0.95,\n        \"rxn_010\": 0.9\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.78,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.84,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.92,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.95,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.84,\n      \"feedback\": \"Conceptually coherent as an inter-environment pathway, but the hydrothermal feedstock step is the weakest element. Literature supports hydrothermal systems mainly as low-flux sources with severe concentration and degradation constraints, so using them conservatively is reasonable, yet direct formaldehyde/formate production at useful levels remains poorly supported.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_001\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Downgrade hydrothermal output to trace feedstock/context rather than productive source\",\n        \"Specify required Fe-S minerals and concentration/export assumptions for rxn_001\",\n        \"Make clearer that downstream surface photochemistry is the productive stage\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P9\",